# Task: Research self-llm GitHub Repository

## Plan
1. [ ] Open https://github.com/datawhalechina/self-llm
2. [ ] Identify core content (Quantization, Fine-tuning, Deployment)
3. [ ] Find tutorials for Gemma and Qwen
4. [ ] Identify scripts for local optimization
5. [ ] Summarize findings briefly

## Findings
- Core Content: Linux-based environment setup, deployment (FastAPI, vLLM, WebDemo), fine-tuning (LoRA, Full-parameter, P-tuning), and integration (LangChain, CLI). Supports specialized hardware: AMD, Ascend, Apple MLX.
- Gemma/Qwen Tutorials: Comprehensive guides for Gemma2 and Qwen2.5 including Lora fine-tuning (PEFT), FastAPI/vLLM deployment, and LangChain integration. Qwen2.5 even has an o1-like reasoning chain tutorial.
- Useful Scripts: `benchmark_throughput.py` (vLLM performance tests), reasoning chain implementation scripts, and `utils.py` for contributor/model management.
